<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Parent Involvement Specialist</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Parent Involvement Specialist<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Barb Ziemke, Parent Trainer and Advocate<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, Salaried Monthly, Exempt status
</p>

<p>This project seeks to improve educational results for children and youth with disabilities from diverse communities through increasing effective parent involvement. It includes providing training and resources to families of students with disabilities from minority, low income, and English language learner backgrounds and the educators who work with their children.</p>

<h3>RESPONSIBILITIES/ROLES</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Coordinate and present trainings to parents and professionals.</li>
	<li>Work effectively with diverse families, communities, and school personnel for improved educational outcomes.</li>
	<li>Ability to form strong, interpersonal relationships</li>
	<li>Provide in-person and phone assistance to parents of children in special education</li>
	<li>Write clear, concise educational material.</li>
	<li>Evaluate project outcome and deliverables.</li>
	<li>Other activities as required.</li>
</ol>

<h3>EXPERIENCE/BACKGROUND SKILLS</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Ability to communicate well with parents of children with disabilities and the professionals who work with their children</li>
	<li> Experience in working with families from diverse cultures</li>
	<li>Experience in public speaking, workshop presentations, and assisting others on the telephone</li>
	<li>Knowledge of laws and rules related to the education of school-age children with disabilities</li>
	<li> Experience and background in research and writing</li>
	<li>Ability to keep good records and collect data in an electronic database for evaluation purposes</li>
	<li>Experience in community service/human service/social service or a helping role</li>
	<li>Excellent organizational skills, ability to meet deadlines</li>
	<li>Ability to apply analytical skills</li>
	<li>Excellent attention to detail</li>
	<li>Working knowledge of Microsoft Word, Outlook and Powerpoint</li>
	<li>Flexible schedule needed to periodically travel and participate in required evening workshops/presentations</li>
	<li> Ability to provide own transportation</li>
	<li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience</li>
</ul>


<p>
Salary to be determined based on experience. Position available immediately.<br />
Parents of children with disabilities and persons of color are encouraged to apply.</p>

<p>
Send resume with a letter of application to:<br />
Mary Jackson| PACER Center, Inc. | 8161 Normandale Blvd. | Minneapolis, MN 55437-1044.
</p>
